        "email": "jpylzhao@fudan",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "We present a sub-exponential forger by using a $k$-sum algorithm\nagainst the aggregate $\\Gamma$-signature, which was proposed at AsiaCCS 2019 by Zhao.\nOur forger is a universal forger under a key-only attack and effective in the knowledge of secret key model. We also discuss the real impact of this attack in reality with   Bitcoin applications.\nThe discussions on the real impact of the attack also highlight the significant differences between the usage of individual signatures like EC-DSA and that of aggregate signatures in the blockchain systems like Bitcoin, which might be of independent interest and could bring forth interesting questions for future investigations.",
    "keywords": [
      "k-sum algorithm",
      "aggregate signature",
      "universal forgery",
      "blockchain"
    ],
    "category": "Public-key cryptography",
